# Personal Reading List Manager

## Project Overview
This is a minimal and easy-to-use web-based tool designed for individual users to track their reading progress. It serves as a simple digital replacement for notebooks or spreadsheets, focusing on clarity, speed, and usability.

## Features
* **Add Books:** Users can add new books with title, author, status (To Read, Reading, Completed), and optional notes.
* **View Books:** All books are displayed in a responsive table.
* **Update Status/Notes:** Users can easily update the reading status and notes for any book.
* **Delete Books:** Remove books from the list with a confirmation.
* **Search/Filter:** Find books by title, author, or status using a search bar and status filter.

## Technologies Used
* **React:** For building the user interface.
* **Standard CSS:** For styling the application.

## Setup and Running Locally
1.  **Clone the repository:**
    ```bash
    git clone [https://github.com/YOUR_USERNAME/personal-reading-list-manager.git](https://github.com/YOUR_USERNAME/personal-reading-list-manager.git)
    cd personal-reading-list-manager
    ```
2.  **Install dependencies:**
    ```bash
    npm install
    ```
3.  **Run the application:**
    ```bash
    npm start
    ```
    The application will typically open in your browser at `http://localhost:3000`.

